properties.description:
Array of conversation messages. Standard shape: `{ id?, content, role: 'user' | 'assistant', timestamp?, attachments? }`. The `role` field drives alignment (user = right, assistant = left). Example message:
```json
{
  "id": "m-42",
  "content": "Here's a quick summary:",
  "role": "assistant",
  "timestamp": "2026-04-23T10:30:00Z",
  "attachments": [
    { "id": "f1", "name": "chart.png", "type": "image/png", "size": 204800, "url": "https://..." }
  ]
}
```
For custom backend shapes, use the `mappingMessage*` formula properties.
